---
title: Mediterranean Quinoa Bowl with Crispy Kale Chips
description: Quinoa bowls are a delicious way to enjoy this protein-rich seed - you can toss in any of your favorite mix-ins! This bowl packs major Mediterranean flavor with briny olives, tomatoes, salty feta, and fresh parsley. A crunchy topping of homemade kale chips adds a special twist to this easy weeknight recipe.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/551c41de6ced6e21538b4569.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/551c41de6ced6e21538b4569.pdf
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mediterranean-quinoa-bowl-551c41de6ced6e21538b4569
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 618 kcal
  fat: 33 g
  carbohydrates: 59 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 10 g
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1 1/2%cups} to a boil
with the @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Add the @quinoa{3/4%cup}, cover, and reduce
to a simmer over medium-low heat for ~{15%minutes}. Set aside.

Meanwhile, remove and discard the stems from @kale{1%bunch}. Tear half the kale
leaves into bite-sized pieces and spread in a single layer on a #baking sheet{}.
Toss with @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} and season with @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. Bake for ~{5-7%minutes}, until crispy and slightly browned. Be
careful not to let them burn!

While the kale bakes, halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch} and
@mixed olives{1%ounce}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the
@parsley{1%bunch}. Thinly slice remaining kale. Don't forget to check on the
kale chips!

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add the
sliced kale and cook, tossing, ~{2-3%minutes} or until softened. Add the garlic,
tomatoes, and @almonds{1%ounce} to the pan and cook, tossing, another
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @red wine vinegar{1%tablespoon} to the pan and stir to combine. Stir in the
parsley, olives, quinoa, and @olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and
pepper.

Divide the quinoa salad between #bowls{} and top with @feta cheese{1/4%cup} and
the crispy kale chips. Enjoy!

> Quinoa bowls are a delicious way to enjoy this protein-rich seed - you can toss
> in any of your favorite mix-ins! This bowl packs major Mediterranean flavor
> with briny olives, tomatoes, salty feta, and fresh parsley. A crunchy topping
> of homemade kale chips adds a special twist to this easy weeknight recipe.